<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Harvest. It's got a permanent slot in my spell lineup, and I love the lil' beggar. But at level 55, I notice maybe 1/3-1/2 of a bubble of mana from it. <br>
<br>
A lot of suggestions have come forward about the Harvest line, and how to fix it. The most common suggestion is to have 3 or 4 spells that scale up. The problem with that, however, is that I would just mem all 3 and use 'em all when they pop.<br>
<br>
Instead, I suggest that Harvest have its cast time reduced as you level up. Leave its mana regen as it is, but have it scale down in casting time to, say, 5 minutes at level 60. I doubt that's really beyond the limitations of the game, since the repop on your spells is server-side.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
2. Root. I like it. Always have. But I think we should have an AE root. I hear people screaming bloody murder, or nerf-bat, but hear me out. I want a PBAE version of the level 4 root. 18-second maximum duration, but unlimited targets surrounding the wizard, and I want it to cast as fast as Jyll's.<br>
<br>
It wouldn't unbalance the game at all, as far as I can see. But it would give wizards an advantage that would make us more desirable in groups: When a bad pull or train comes along, and the group has to train, the wizard can step in, root 'em all in a couple seconds, and give the group an 18-second head start. The duration of this root could be upped to 30 seconds or so, I suppose. It still isn't that unbalancing.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Thoughts? Opinions? Am I on crack? <p><center><a href="http://orderofantondwer.cjb.net" target=_new>
